HEADWORD: Arctation
<hw>Arc*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arctus</ets> shut in, narrow, p. p. of <ets>arcere</ets> to shut
in: cf. F. <ets>arctation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Constriction or contraction of some natural passage, as in
constipation from inflammation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arctic</ent>⟦br⟧
